# Pre-commit Hooks — Recommendation for {{PROJECT_NAME}}

Pre-commit hooks catch formatting errors, lint violations, and broken tests before they reach CI, shortening the feedback loop for every contributor.

---

{{#IF_RUST}}
## Rust — lefthook (recommended)

Install: `cargo install lefthook` or grab the binary from <https://github.com/evilmartians/lefthook/releases>.

`lefthook.yml`:

```yaml
pre-commit:
  commands:
    fmt-check:
      run: cargo fmt --check
    clippy:
      run: cargo clippy -- -D warnings
    test-compile:
      run: cargo test --no-run
pre-push:
  commands:
    test:
      run: {{TEST_CMD}}
```

`--no-run` compiles tests without running them, keeping the pre-commit hook fast.
{{/IF_RUST}}

{{#IF_TS}}
## TypeScript / Node — lefthook or husky + lint-staged (recommended)

**Option A — lefthook** (`npm install -D lefthook`):

```yaml
pre-commit:
  commands:
    lint:
      glob: "*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}"
      run: {{LINT_CMD}} {staged_files}
pre-push:
  commands:
    test:
      run: {{TEST_CMD}}
```

**Option B — husky + lint-staged** (`{{PACKAGE_MANAGER}} add -D husky lint-staged`):

`.lintstagedrc.json`: `{ "*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}": ["{{LINT_CMD}}"] }`

`.husky/pre-push`: `{{TEST_CMD}}`
{{/IF_TS}}

{{#IF_GO}}
## Go — lefthook (recommended)

Install: `go install github.com/evilmartians/lefthook@latest`.

`lefthook.yml`:

```yaml
pre-commit:
  commands:
    fmt-check:
      run: test -z "$(gofmt -l .)"
    vet:
      run: go vet ./...
pre-push:
  commands:
    test:
      run: {{TEST_CMD}}
```
{{/IF_GO}}

{{#IF_PYTHON}}
## Python — pre-commit.com (recommended)

Install: `pip install pre-commit` then `pre-commit install`.

`.pre-commit-config.yaml`:

```yaml
repos:
  - repo: https://github.com/astral-sh/ruff-pre-commit
    rev: v0.4.0
    hooks:
      - id: ruff
        args: [--fix]
      - id: ruff-format
  - repo: https://github.com/pre-commit/mirrors-mypy
    rev: v1.10.0
    hooks:
      - id: mypy
        additional_dependencies: []
```

Pre-push: add a `.git/hooks/pre-push` that runs `{{TEST_CMD}}`, or manage via lefthook alongside pre-commit.com.
{{/IF_PYTHON}}

---

Install manually — the init workflow deliberately does NOT install hooks automatically. Review the snippet for your ecosystem above, adapt paths and commands to your project layout, then commit the hook config alongside your code. Refer to `AGENTS.md` for this project's commit message rules and branching conventions.
